 step i.e. Smart Total Elite Protection offers neither top-up nor life stage.

49
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:06,800
 Both life stage and top-ups are capped to a specific amount and subject to conditions,

50
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:10,480
 and the premiums increase proportionally when the sum assured is increased.

51
00:03:10,480 --> 00:03:19,760
 There is also the zero cost option, in which you receive all premiums back at no additional expense.

52
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:25,520
 Most leading term plans include the zero cost option, though it comes with very specific terms

53
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:29,840
 and conditions that vary among insurers. These conditions typically specify the minimum

54
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:34,320
 duration the policy must be held, conditions for exiting the plan and other factors.

55
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:39,040
 Nevertheless, as an inbuilt feature, this zero cost option is beneficial to have

56
00:03:39,040 --> 00:03:42,320
 and provides flexibility to exit the plan if necessary.

57
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:47,440
 HDFC Care to Protect Smart, ICICI iProtect Smart, Max Life Insurance, Smart Total Elite

58
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:50,160
 Protection, and Bajaj Etouch offer it inbuilt.

59
00:03:50,160 --> 00:03:54,640
 Lastly, there is Terminal Illness. This is when a medical practitioner believes that a person is

60
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:59,440
 going to die within six months due to any terminal illness, and the insurer will release the sum

61
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:04,080
 insured to the holder and the family upon the certification from the medical practitioner.

62
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:08,880
 However, the likelihood of a medical practitioner issuing such a certification is relatively low.

63
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:14,000
 While the rider may not seem practical, it is an inbuilt feature with most of the plans which comes

64
