 numerous illnesses on rice. God forbid someone gets cancer and they're not able to work, there is no

69
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:47,440
 income, then who will look after the family? That is where the critical illness rider comes in.

70
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:53,440
 The critical illness feature provides a lump sum payout upon diagnosis of any critical illness.

71
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:59,040
 Specified in the policy document, this amount can be utilized without any restrictions imposed by

72
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:04,000
 the insurer. Policyholders can use it for income replacement or to cover additional medical expenses

73
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:08,000
 arising from the critical illness. Although you can argue that the cost of the medical expenses

74
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:12,800
 can be taken care by comprehensive health insurance, critical illness feature is still useful

75
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:17,840
 as an income replacement during tough times. There is another rider which is a cost-effective

76
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:22,480
 option and has beneficial additions to a term insurance policy considering its price and

77
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:28,240
 functioning. At Ditto, we strongly recommend this rider to be included in the term plan. This is

78
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:33,600
 waiver of premium. This feature ensures that all future premiums are waived off if the policyholder

79
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:38,880
 is diagnosed with a critical illness or suffers from total permanent disability, mostly due to an

80
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:43,920
 accident as specified in the policy document. Some term plans cover both critical illness and total

81
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:48,720
 permanent disabilities due to accidents, while others only cover total permanent disabilities

82
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:55,760
 due to accidents or terminal illness. Now you see you can always opt in for a pure margarita pizza

